==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pule
<hw>Pule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Puled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Puling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>piauler</ets>; cf. L.
<ets>pipilare</ets>, <ets>pipire</ets>, to peep, pip, chirp, and E.
<ets>peep</ets> to chirp.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cry like a
chicken.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To whimper; to whine, as a complaining
child.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It becometh not such a gallant to whine and <qex>pule</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puler</ent>⟦br⟧
